last_episode_to_air.name: If You Don't Give Up
last_episode_to_air.overview: Hae-young is in critical condition after being shot while meeting with Sung-bum. In 2000, Jae-han has been captured by Bum-joo.

name: Signal
overview: Detectives from the present and a detective from the past communicate via walkie-talkie to solve a long-time unsolved case.
tagline: There are those who are born monsters, but there are also those who are made into monsters by people.

episodes.name: You're Doomed
episodes.overview: Profiler Park Hae-young hears a man calling his name through a discarded two-way radio. The voice starts talking about an unsolved crime.

episodes.name: We Still Have a Chance
episodes.overview: The statute of limitations is lifted after the suspect's arrest. Hae-young joins Soo-hyun's team for the newly established cold case squad.

episodes.name: We Can Prevent the Killings
episodes.overview: Reality changes after Hae-young exchanges information with Jae-han. Hae-young tries to work together with Jae-han in 1989 to prevent the next murder.

episodes.name: We Found the Killer
episodes.overview: The ninth victim is Won-kyung, the woman Jae-han loves. A driver turns himself in, but Soo-hyun and Jae-han determine that his son is the real killer.

episodes.name: Changing the Past Alters the Present
episodes.overview: Hae-young starts to investigate Jae-han's disappearance. Jae-han's former colleagues get suspicious about seeing Hae-young digging into the past.

episodes.name: Catch Him by All Means
episodes.overview: Seeking vengeance for the events that lead to the death of his daughter, Kyung-tae commits a kidnapping after getting out of prison for burglary.

episodes.name: We Must Dig Deeper
episodes.overview: Jae-han arrests Se-kyu for the serial burglary case, but the culprit is freed after serving a short sentence; Kyung-tae still commits murder.

episodes.name: How Are You Alive?
episodes.overview: Soo-hyun and Hae-young notice a connection between the burglary case and Da-hye, the woman who killed herself twenty years ago.

episodes.name: Hongwon Dong Case
episodes.overview: Hae-young learns that Chi-soo and Jae-han met in 1999 during a case in Inju. After serving time for the crime, Hae-young's brother had killed himself.

episodes.name: Someone Has to Stop the Bad Guys
episodes.overview: The bodies discovered in the mountains appear to be more victims of the 1997 serial murder case. Jae-han learns that Soo-hyun became team leader.

episodes.name: The One Last Case
episodes.overview: Hae-young and Soo-hyun arrest Jin-woo after coming to the conclusion that he is the killer. Hae-young asks Jae-han about the Inju rape case.

episodes.name: The Case Was Manipulated
episodes.overview: Hae-young becomes a suspect for the murder of Chi-soo. Jae-han realizes who the principle offender of the attack on Hye-seung is.

episodes.name: The Real Assailant
episodes.overview: Soo-hyun and the others mourn after confirming that the remains belong to Jae-han. Hae-young learns that Jae-han used to look after him in the past.

episodes.name: Not Now, But Maybe In The Past
episodes.overview: Hae-young realizes the possibility that his brother could have been murdered after learning from Hye-seung that Sun-woo was not guilty.

episodes.name: Is It Really You?
episodes.overview: Hae-young is arrested for the murder of Chi-soo. Soo-hyun hears Jae-han apologizing over the radio for not being able to prevent Sun-woo's death.

episodes.name: If You Don't Give Up
episodes.overview: Hae-young is in critical condition after being shot while meeting with Sung-bum. In 2000, Jae-han has been captured by Bum-joo.
